on Internationale de Football Association |date=26 September 2003 |accessdate=29 October 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041015225548/http://fifaworldcup.yahoo.com/03/en/030926/1/9xi.html |archivedate=15 October 2004}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Assistant referee (association football)|Assistant referee]]s:'''\n<br />{{flagicon|ARG}} Sabrina Lois ([[Argentine Football Association|Argentina]])\n<br />{{flagicon|ARG}} Alejandra Cercato ([[Argentine Football Association|Argentina]])\n<br />'''[[Assistant referee (association football)#Fourth official|Fourth official]]:'''\n<br />{{flagicon|KOR}} Im Eun-Ju ([[Korea Football Association|South Korea]])\n|}\n\n===Sweden vs Nigeria===\n<section begin=A5 />{{Football box\n|date={{Start date|2003|9|28|df=y}}\n|time=13:00 <includeonly>[[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]] ([[UTC\u221204:00|UTC\u22124]])</includeonly>\n|team1={{fbw-rt|SWE}}\n|score={{score link|2003 FIFA Women's World Cup Group A#Sweden vs Nigeria|3\u20130}}\n|report=https://www.fifa.com/womensworldcup/matches/round=69290100/match=69290021/index.html\n|team2={{fbw|NGA}}\n|goals1=\n*[[Hanna Ljungberg|Ljungberg]] {{goal|56||79}}\n*[[Malin Mostr\u00f6m|Mostr\u00f6m]] {{goal|81}}\n|goals2=\n|stadium=[[Mapfre Stadium|Columbus Crew Stadium]], [[Columbus, Ohio|Columbus]]\n|attendance=22,828<ref name=\"TR03\"/>\n|referee=[[Sonia Denoncourt]] ([[Canadian Soccer Association|Canada]])\n}}<section end=A5 />\n\n{| width=\"100%\"\n|valign=\"top\" width=\"40%\"|\n{| style=\"font-size:90%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"\n|-\n!width=25| !!width=25|\n|-\n|GK ||'''1''' ||[[Caroline J\u00f6nsson]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''4''' ||[[Hanna Marklund]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''2''' ||[[Karolina Westberg]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''5''' ||[[Kristin Bengtsson]] || || {{suboff|46}}\n|-\n|DF ||'''19'''||Sara Call\n|-\n|DF ||'''7''' ||[[Sara Larsson]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''18'''||[[Frida \u00d6stberg]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''9''' ||[[Malin Andersson]] ([[Captain (association football)|c]])&nbsp; || || {{suboff|66}}\n|-\n|MF ||'''6''' ||[[Malin 